Multithreading

1. What is a process?

   A process is usally an program or a task which is running independently  on  the operating system. It is composed of multiple threads.
   examples: SkypeApp.exe
   Each process has a PID (process id)


2. What is a Thread?

   A thread is an independent path of execution within a program.
 

